<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-362-022  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 362 022.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 19 1989 n320 p55(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOC looks to level the field. (US Department of Commerce)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rohm, Wendy Goldman.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>In an effort to reduce the growing US trade deficit, the USDepartment of Commerce is stepping up efforts to promote exportsof US high technology goods.andP;  The department has sponsored trademissions, primarily to advance microcomputer products to LatinAmerica, India and the Soviet Union.andP;  These missions are designedto bring together buyers of high technology goods with their USsellers.andP;  Vendors participating in the mission are charged a feeto cover costs of the mission.andP;  Most of the vendors participatingare smaller entities, as larger corporations tend to support theirown trade efforts.andP;  In addition to the trade missions, theDepartment of Commerce has focused on decontrolling licensedproducts and easing other export restrictions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     International TradeHigh TechnologyPromotion of ProductGovernment AgencyMarket ValueInternationalUnited States. Department of Commerce.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   International revenue (of US companies) (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>